  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: d0ec49142d5c7c24fb05ee739840cab0, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Impending Doom of Samaria and Jerusalem'
      title: The Impending Doom of Samaria and Jerusalem
      number: 1
      content: 'The word of Yahweh that came to Micah the Morashtite in the days
        of Jotham, Ahaz, and Hezekiah, the kings of Judah, that he saw concerning
        Samaria and Jerusalem: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Hear, all you peoples; give heed, O earth and its fullness. And let
        the Lord Yahweh be against you as a witness, the Lord from his holy temple.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For behold, Yahweh is coming out from his place, and he will come
        down and tread upon the high places of the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The mountains will melt under him and the valleys will burst open,
        like wax before the fire, like water rushing down a slope. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'All this is for the rebellion of Jacob, and for the sins of the house
        of Israel. What is the rebellion of Jacob? Is it not Samaria? And what are
        the high places of Judah? Are they not Jerusalem? '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So I will make Samaria as a heap of rubble in the field, a place
        for planting a vineyard. And I will pour down her stones into the valley
        and uncover her foundations. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then all her idols will be broken in pieces, and all her prostitution
        wages will be burned in the fire, and all her idols I will make a desolation,
        For from the wage of a prostitute she gathered them, and to the wage of a
        prostitute they will return. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'On account of this I will lament and wail. I will go about barefoot
        and naked. I will make a lamentation like the jackals, and a mourning ceremony
        like the ostriches.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For her wounds are incurable, because it has come to Judah. It has
        reached to the gate of my people, to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Do not tell it in Gath; you must not weep at all. In Beth-le-Aphrah
        roll yourself in dust. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Pass on, you inhabitants of Shaphir, in naked shame. The inhabitants
        of Zaanan do not come forth; the wailing of Beth-ha-Ezel will take its protection
        from you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For the inhabitants of Maroth writhed for good, because disaster
        has come down from Yahweh to the gate of Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Harness the chariot to the team of horses, O inhabitants of Lachish;
        it is the beginning of sin for the daughter of Zion, for the transgressions
        of Israel were found in you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Therefore you will give parting gifts to Moresheth-Gath; the houses
        of Achzib will be a deception to the kings of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'I will again bring the conqueror upon you, O inhabitants of Mareshah;
        the glory of Israel will come to Adullam. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Make yourselves bald and cut off your hair for the children of your
        pleasure. Expand your baldness as the eagle, for they will go into exile
        away from you. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Woe to the Oppressors of God\u2019s People"
      title: "Woe to the Oppressors of God\u2019s People"
      number: 1
      content: 'Woe to those who plan wickedness and evil deeds upon their beds!
        In the light of the morning they did it, because they have power in their
        hands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'They covet fields and seize them, and houses, and they take them
        away. They oppress a man and his house; a man and his inheritance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Therefore, thus says Yahweh: Look! I am planning disaster against
        this family from which you will not be able to remove your necks. You will
        not walk proudly, for it is a time of disaster. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "In that day they will raise a proverb against you, and will wail
        a bitter wailing, saying, \u201CWe are utterly ruined; he exchanges the portion
        of my people. How he removes it from me; he apportions our field to an apostate.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Therefore you will have no one casting a line by lot in the assembly
        of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CDo not preach!\u201D they are preaching. They should not preach
        to these; disgrace will not overtake us. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Should this be said, O house of Jacob? Is the patience of Yahweh
        shortened? Are these his deeds? Are my words not pleasing to him who walks
        upright? '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But recently my people have risen up as an enemy; from before the
        cloak you strip off the robe from those passing by in confidence, returning
        from war. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'You have driven out the women of my people from the houses of their
        pleasure. From their children you have taken away my glory forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Arise and go, for this is no resting place, on account of uncleanness
        that destroys with painful destruction. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "If a man walks about in a spirit of deception and lies, saying \u201CI
        will preach to you of wine and strong drink,\u201D then he would be a preacher
        for this people! "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'I will surely gather all of you, O Jacob; I will surely gather together
        the remainder of Israel. I will set them like sheep of Bozrah. Like a herd
        in the midst of their pasture they will be in tumult from people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The one who breaks out before them goes up; they break through and
        pass the gate, going out through it. Their king passes before them, Yahweh
        at their head. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Israel\u2019s Leaders Denounced"
      title: "Israel\u2019s Leaders Denounced"
      number: 1
      content: "And I said, \u201CListen, O heads of Jacob and leaders of the house
        of Israel! Is it not for you to know justice? "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Those of you who are haters of good and lovers of evil, who tear
        their skin from them and their flesh from their bones, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and who eat the flesh of my people, and strip their skin from them,
        and break their bones, and chop them like meat in the pot, and like flesh
        in the midst of a cooking pot.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then they will cry to Yahweh, but he will not answer them. He will
        hide his face from them at that time, when they have made their deeds evil. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Thus says Yahweh concerning the prophets who are leading my people
        astray, who are biting with their teeth and proclaim, \u201CPeace,\u201D
        but whoever puts nothing into their mouths they declare war against. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Therefore it will be as night to you, without vision, and darkness
        to you, without divination. And the sun will set on the prophets, and the
        day will grow dark over them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then the seers will be disgraced, and those practicing divination
        will be put to shame. All of them will cover their lips, for there is no
        reply from God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But I, I am filled with power, with the Spirit of Yahweh, and with
        justice and might, to declare to Jacob his rebellion, and to Israel his sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Hear this, O rulers of the house of Jacob and leaders of the house
        of Israel, those detesting justice and perverting all that is right, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'he who builds Zion with blood and Jerusalem with wickedness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Its rulers judge for a bribe; its priests teach for a price; its
        prophets practice divination for money. But they lean on Yahweh, saying,
        \u201CIs not Yahweh in our midst? Disaster will not come upon us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Therefore on account of you Zion will be plowed as a field, and Jerusalem
        will be a heap of rubble, and the temple mount as a high place in a forest. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Mountain of Yahweh'
      title: The Mountain of Yahweh
      number: 1
      content: 'And it will be that at the end of those days, the mountain of Yahweh
        will be established as the highest of the mountains, and it will be lifted
        up above the hills, and people will stream to it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And many nations will come and say, \u201CCome! Let us go up to the
        mountain of Yahweh, and to the temple of the God of Jacob, that he may teach
        us his ways, and that we may walk in his paths,\u201D for the law will go
        out from Zion, and the word of Yahweh from Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And he will judge between many peoples and will arbitrate for strong
        nations far away; and they will beat their swords into plowshares and their
        spears into pruning hooks; nation will not lift up a sword against a nation,
        and they will no longer learn war. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But they will sit, each under his vine and under his fig tree, and
        no one will make them afraid, for the mouth of Yahweh of hosts has spoken. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Yahweh Will Deliver Zion'
      title: Yahweh Will Deliver Zion
      number: 5
      content: 'For all the nations walk, each in the name of its god, but we will
        walk in the name of Yahweh our God, forever and ever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CIn that day,\u201D declares Yahweh,  \u201CI will assemble
        the one who limps, and I will gather the one who has been scattered, and
        those whom I have mistreated. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And I will make the one who limps a remnant, and the one driven far
        away a strong nation, and Yahweh will reign over them on Mount Zion from
        now to forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And you, O Migdal-Eder,  hill of the daughter of Zion, to you it
        will come, and the former dominion will come, the reign of the daughter of
        Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So then, why do you shout a loud shout? Is there no king in you?
        Has your counselor perished that pangs like a woman in labor have seized
        you? '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Writhe and groan, O daughter of Zion, like a woman in labor. For
        now you will go forth from the city, and you will camp in the field; you
        will go to Babylon. There you will be rescued; there Yahweh will redeem you
        from the hand of your enemies. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And now, many nations are gathered against you who are saying, \u2018Let
        her be defiled, and let our eyes gaze upon Zion.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But they do not know the thoughts of Yahweh, and they do not understand
        his plan, that he has gathered them as sheaves to his threshing floor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Arise and thresh, O daughter of Zion, for your horn I will make as
        iron and your hooves as bronze. And you will break many peoples in pieces,
        and their gain you will devote to destruction to Yahweh, and their wealth
        to the Lord of the whole earth.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Ruler from Bethlehem'
      title: A Ruler from Bethlehem
      number: 1
      content: ' Now muster troops, O daughter of troops; a siege he puts against
        us. They strike the ruler of Israel with a rod on the cheek. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'But you, O Bethlehem Ephrathah, too small to be among the clans of
        Judah, from you one will go out for me, to be ruler in Israel; and his origins
        are from of old, from ancient days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Therefore he will give them up until the time of she who is with
        child has given birth. And the rest of his brothers will return to the children
        of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And he will stand and shepherd his flock in the strength of Yahweh,
        in the majesty of the name of Yahweh his God. And they will live, for now
        he will be great unto the ends of the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And this one will be peace. As for the Assyrian, when he comes into
        our land and when he treads on our fortresses, then we will raise up against
        him seven shepherds and eight leaders of men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: A Remnant Delivered'
      title: A Remnant Delivered
      number: 6
      content: 'And they will shepherd the land of Assyria with the sword, and the
        land of Nimrod at its entrances. And he will rescue us from the Assyrian 
        when he comes into our land, and when they tread upon our border. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And the remnant of Jacob will be in the midst of many nations, like
        dew from Yahweh, like showers upon the grass which does not wait for a man,
        nor delays for the children of humankind. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And the remnant of Jacob will be among the nations, in the midst
        of many peoples, like a lion among the wild animals of the forest, like a
        young lion among the herds of sheep which, when it passes through and treads
        down and tears in pieces, there is none who can deliver. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Your hand will be lifted high over your enemies, and all your foes
        will be cut off. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CAnd it will happen that in that day,\u201D declares Yahweh,
        \u201Cthen I will cut off your horses from among you, and I will destroy
        your chariots. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And I will cut off the cities of your land, and I will demolish all
        your fortifications. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And I will cut off sorceries from your hand, and you will not have
        soothsayers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And I will cut off your idols and your stone pillars from among you,
        and you will no longer bow down to the work of your hands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And I will uproot your Asherahs from among you, and I will destroy
        your cities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And in anger and in wrath I will execute vengeance on the nations
        who did not obey.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Yahweh Brings a Charge against Israel'
      title: Yahweh Brings a Charge against Israel
      number: 1
      content: "Hear now what Yahweh says: \u201CArise! Plead your case with the
        mountains, and let the hills hear your voice.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Hear, O mountains, the indictment of Yahweh, and you eternal foundations
        of the earth, for Yahweh has an indictment against his people, and against
        Israel he contends. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CO my people, what have I done to you, and how have I wearied
        you? Answer me! "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For I brought you up from the land of Egypt, and from the house of
        slavery I redeemed you. And I sent Moses, Aaron, and Miriam before you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: What Does Yahweh Require?'
      title: What Does Yahweh Require?
      number: 5
      content: "O my people, remember what Balak the king of Moab devised, and what
        Balaam the son of Beor answered him, and what happened from Shittim to Gilgal,
        so that you might know the righteous acts of Yahweh.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'With what shall I approach Yahweh, and bow down to God on high? Shall
        I approach him with burnt offerings, with bull calves a year old? '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Will Yahweh be pleased with thousands of rams, with myriads of rivers
        of oil? Shall I give my firstborn for my transgression, the fruit of my body
        for the sin of my soul? '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: The Destruction of the Wicked'
      title: The Destruction of the Wicked
      number: 8
      content: 'He has told you, O mortal, what is good, and what does Yahweh ask
        from you but to do justice, and to love kindness, and to walk humbly with
        your God? '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "The voice of Yahweh calls to the city (it is sound judgment to fear
        your name): \u201CHear, O staff! Now who has appointed it? "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Is there any longer a man in the house of the wicked treasures of
        wickedness, and the ephah of scarcity which is accursed?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Shall I regard as pure the one with scales of wickedness, and with
        a bag of deceitful weights? '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Because her rich are full of violence, and her inhabitants speak
        lies, and their tongue is deceitful in their mouth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And I also have made you sick by striking you down,  making you desolate
        because of your sins. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'You yourself will eat but not be satisfied; your hunger will be in
        your midst, and you will put away, but you will not save, and what you save
        I will hand over to the sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'You yourself will sow, but you will not reap; you will tread olives,
        but you will not anoint yourself with oil; you will tread grapes, but you
        will not drink wine. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For you have observed the regulations of Omri and all the works of
        the house of Ahab. And you have walked in their counsels, so that I am making
        you a desolation and your inhabitants an object of scorn. So you will bear
        the scorn of my people. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Wait Upon Yahweh'
      title: Wait Upon Yahweh
      number: 1
      content: 'Woe is me! For I have become like the gatherings of summer, like
        the gleanings of the grape harvest, when there is no cluster of grapes to
        eat or early ripened fruit that my soul desires. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The faithful person has perished from the land, and there is none
        who is upright among humankind. All of them lie in wait; each hunts his brother
        with a net. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Their hands are upon evil, to do it well; the official and the judge
        ask for the bribe, and the great man utters the evil desire of his soul;
        and they weave it together. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The best of them is like a brier; the most upright worse than a thorn
        hedge. The day of your watchman, your punishment, has come; now their confusion
        will come. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Do not put faith in a friend; put no trust in a close friend. Guard
        the doorways of your mouth from the one who lies in your lap. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For a son treats a father with contempt; a daughter rises up against
        her mother, a daughter-in-law against her mother-in-law; the enemies of a
        man are the men of his own house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But as for me, I will look to Yahweh; I will wait for the God of
        my salvation. My God will hear me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'You should not rejoice over me, O my enemy! When I fall I will stand
        up; when I sit in darkness Yahweh will be a light for me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'I will bear the rage of Yahweh, for I have sinned against him, until
        he pleads my cause and executes my justice. He will bring me out to the light;
        I will see his righteousness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then my enemy will see, and shame will cover her who said to me,
        \u201CWhere is Yahweh your God?\u201D My eyes will look upon her; now she
        will become a trampling place, like mud in the streets. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'A day for building your walls; on that day he will extend your boundary. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'On that day he will come to you from Assyria and the cities of Egypt,
        and from Egypt to the River, and from sea to sea and mountain to mountain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'But the earth will be a desolation because of its inhabitants, for
        the fruit of their deeds. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Shepherd your people with your staff, the flock of your inheritance,
        those dwelling alone in a forest in the midst of Carmel. Let them feed in
        Bashan and Gilead, as in the days of old. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'As in the days when you came out from the land of Egypt I will show
        him wondrous things. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The nations will see and be ashamed because of all their might. They
        will lay the hand on the mouth; their ears will be deaf. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'They will lick the dust like the serpent, like the crawling things
        of the earth. They will come trembling from their strongholds to Yahweh our
        God. Let them fear and be afraid of you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Who is a God like you, forgiving sin and passing over rebellion for
        the remnant of his inheritance? He does not retain his anger forever, for
        he delights in loyal love. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'He will again have compassion on us; he will trample our iniquities.
        And you will hurl all their sins in the depths of the sea. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'You will show faithfulness to Jacob, and loyal love to Abraham, as
        you have sworn to our ancestors  from the days of old. '
      comments: []
